## Problem
B069 survey: Vosk small en-us mangles product wake names (`hark`→hook/hawk, `herald`→harold). Alias/learning papers over weak open-vocab ASR. **Sherpa-ONNX open-vocab KWS** (English GigaSpeech 3.3M int8) matched all 7 current live wake fixtures correctly at RTF≈0.02 and ~half Vosk RSS.

See `docs/plans/B069-local-stt-survey.md`.

## Goal
Ship optional ambient wake engine `sherpa_kws` implementing `WakeBackend`, without flipping the default off Vosk until dogfood — plus first-run setup so operators can choose the engine without hand-editing config.

## Already on master (do not re-do)

| Item | Evidence |
|------|----------|
| `DEFAULT_WAKE_NAMES = (iris, mercury, hark, herald)` | `wake.py`, `config.py` (`cbeb65a`) |
| Product phrases include hey/hello/okay iris & mercury | `wake.py` |
| Default TTS example voice **eve**; persona pairing Iris→eve, Mercury→leo (docs/comments) | `config.py` template + CHANGELOG |
| TTS sample layout `assets/tts/samples/{provider}/{gender}/{voice}.mp3` | `cbeb65a` |
| B069 survey + KWS measurements | `docs/plans/B069-local-stt-survey.md` |

**Not done:** Sherpa backend, download script, `engine=sherpa_kws`, doctor, fixture mark, `hark setup`, SETUP.md / WAKE_STT.md, setup-complete version flag.

## Scope (remaining)

### A. Sherpa KWS wake backend (core)
- Optional dependency / download script for `sherpa-onnx-kws-zipformer-gigaspeech-3.3M-2024-01-01` (int8)
- Build keywords file from `WakePolicy` (names×prefixes + exact phrases); rebuild on config watch / SIGHUP
- `engine = "sherpa_kws"` in `[ambient]`; doctor readiness when selected
- Fixture tests (optional mark if model missing), keep text-path tests engine-agnostic
- Preserve fail-open: missing model → clear error / fall back path documented
- Vosk remains **default** until dogfood says otherwise

### B. Guided setup — `hark setup` + skill docs
Fold first-run / Mode A setup so Sherpa is choosable at install time.

1. Writes/updates `~/.config/hark/config.toml`
2. Writes **`~/.local/state/hark/setup-complete.json`** with at least:
   - `hark_version` (version that produced the flag)
   - `completed_at`
   - answers snapshot (wake engine, names, voice, sessions summary — no secrets)
3. On later runs / Mode A start: if flag missing **or** `hark_version` is older than
   current in a way that adds new setup questions → re-prompt only the **new** questions.

**Setup question order** (canonical agent+CLI script in `skill/hark/SETUP.md`, package mirror):

1. Health (`hark doctor`) — text OK
2. **Herdr sessions** — local / SSH / mix
3. **Persona** — feminine (Iris+eve) vs masculine (Mercury+leo) vs custom name
4. **TTS voice** — list available voices for chosen/auto provider; play short sample optional
5. **Wake backend** — **Vosk** vs **Sherpa KWS** (extensible); recommend Sherpa when download OK; Vosk if constrained; allow defer
6. Download/install model if Sherpa selected; set `[ambient] engine`
7. Confirm wake test (“say hey iris / hey mercury”)
8. Write setup-complete flag with version
9. Arm Mode A monitors (skill continues)

Voice-first after doctor when Mode A skill drives setup (TTS questions one at a time).

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `skill/hark/SETUP.md` (+ package mirror) | Question script, order, config keys, setup-complete schema |
| `skill/hark/WAKE_STT.md` (or `LOCAL_STT.md`) | Vosk / Sherpa KWS / faster-whisper / Moonshine requirements, size, when to pick; link B069 survey |

SKILL.md links both; SETUP is the agent checklist.

### Product defaults (verify only — mostly landed)

| Role | Wake name | Default TTS voice (xAI) |
|------|-----------|-------------------------|
| Feminine (default) | **Iris** | **eve** |
| Masculine | **Mercury** | **leo** |
| Product aliases | hark, herald | — |

- Operator may pick **any** TTS voice from the active provider catalog.
- Setup feminine path → Iris + eve; masculine → Mercury + leo (unless customized).

